ucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dagrimm%26avatarId%3D10500%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/0e947b5413f5d57fba29a8ea5412f773?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Dagrimm%26avatarId%3D10500%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Andy Grimm","active":false,"timeZone":"America/New_York"},"body":"Originally posted on 2012-03-17 22:42:15 by bteachenor\n\nSat Mar 17 15:42:14 2012: Request 6655 was acted upon.\n Transaction: Ticket created by bill.teachenor\n       Queue: Feature Requests\n     Subject: Allow registration of CC using its DNS name\n       Owner: Nobody\n  Requestors: bill.teachenor@eucalyptus.com\n      Status: new\n Ticket <URL: https://support.eucalyptus.com/Ticket/Display.html?id=6655 >\n\n\nI've attempted to register all the cloud components using DNS names, instead of\nIP addresses.\n\nIt seems that this works for all components, except for the CC.\n\nWhen registering the CC using its DNS name, the forwarding rules are not added\nto iptables for security groups.\n\nAlthough the installation documentation specifies that you should use IP\naddresses, many administrators would prefer to use DNS names to ease management\nin their environments.\n\nBill\n\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=agrimm","name":"agrimm","key":"agrimm","accountId":"557058:9ebc3512-73d8-45c9-85de-4325aaa62488","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/0e947b5413f5d57fba29a8ea5412f773?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dagrimm%26avatarId%3D10500%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/0e947b5413f5d57fba29a8ea5412f773?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dagrimm%26avatarId%3D10500%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/0e947b5413f5d57fba29a8ea5412f773?s